SIMPLE: glow
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glow
<hw>Glow</hw> <pr>(gl⟦omac⟧)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Glowed</conjf> <pr>(gl⟦omac⟧d)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Glowing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS.
<ets>gl⟦omac⟧wan</ets>; akin to D. <ets>gloeijen</ets>, OHG.
<ets>gluoen</ets>, G. <ets>gl⟦uum⟧hen</ets>, Icel. <ets>gl⟦omac⟧a</ets>,
Dan. <ets>gloende</ets> glowing. ⟦root⟧94. Cf.
<er>Gloom</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To shine with an intense or white heat; to give
forth vivid light and heat; to be incandescent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Glows</qex> in the stars, and blossoms in the trees.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To exhibit a strong, bright color; to be brilliant,
as if with heat; to be bright or red with heat or animation, with
blushes, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Clad in a gown that <qex>glows</qex> with Tyrian rays.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>glow</qex> with shame of your proceedings.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To feel hot; to have a burning sensation, as of the
skin, from friction, exercise, etc.; to burn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Did not his temples <qex>glow</qex>⟦br⟧
In the same sultry winds and acrching heats?</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The cord slides swiftly through his <qex>glowing</qex> hands.</q>
<rj><qau>Gay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To feel the heat of passion; to be animated, as by
intense love, zeal, anger, etc.; to rage, as passior; <as>as, the heart
<ex>glows</ex> with love, zeal, or patriotism</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With pride it mounts, and with revenge it <qex>glows</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Burns with one love, with one resentment <qex>glows</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Glow
<hw>Glow</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To make hot; to flush.</def>
<mark>[Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fans, whose wind did seem⟦br⟧
To <qex>glow</qex> the delicate cheeks which they did cool.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glow</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Glow
<hw>Glow</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>White or red heat;
incandscence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Brightness or warmth of color; redness; a rosy
flush; <as>as, the <ex>glow</ex> of health in the cheeks</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Intense excitement or earnestness; vehemence or heat
of passion; ardor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The red <qex>glow</qex> of scorn.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Heat of body; a sensation of warmth, as that
produced by exercise, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glowbard</ent>⟦br⟧
